31/* Data structure for recording the patterns of insns that have CLOBBERs.
32 We use this to output a function that adds these CLOBBERs to a
33 previously-allocated PARALLEL expression. */
34
35struct clobber_pat
36{
37 struct clobber_ent *insns;
38 rtx pattern;
39 int first_clobber;
40 struct clobber_pat *next;
41 int has_hard_reg;
42} *clobber_list;
43
44/* Records one insn that uses the clobber list. */
45
46struct clobber_ent
47{
48 int code_number; /* Counts only insns. */
49 struct clobber_ent *next;
50};
51
52static void output_peephole2_scratches (rtx);
53
54/* True for <X>_optab if that optab isn't allowed to fail. */
55static bool nofail_optabs[NUM_OPTABS];
56
57static void
58print_code (RTX_CODE code)
59{
60 const char *p1;
61 for (p1 = GET_RTX_NAME (code); *p1; p1++)
62 putchar (TOUPPER (*p1));
63}
64
65static void
66gen_rtx_scratch (rtx x, enum rtx_code subroutine_type)
67{
68 if (subroutine_type == DEFINE_PEEPHOLE2)
69 {
70 printf ("operand%d", XINT (x, 0));
71 }
72 else
73 {
74 printf ("gen_rtx_SCRATCH (%smode)", GET_MODE_NAME (GET_MODE (x)));
75 }
76}
77
78/* Print a C expression to construct an RTX just like X,
79 substituting any operand references appearing within. */
80
81static void
82gen_exp (rtx x, enum rtx_code subroutine_type, char *used)
83{
84 RTX_CODE code;
85 int i;
86 int len;
87 const char *fmt;
88 const char *sep = "";
89
90 if (x == 0)
91 {
92 printf ("NULL_RTX");
93 return;
94 }
95
96 code = GET_CODE (x);
97
98 switch (code)
99 {
100 case MATCH_OPERAND:
101 case MATCH_DUP:
102 if (used)
103 {
104 if (used[XINT (x, 0)])
105 {
106 printf ("copy_rtx (operand%d)", XINT (x, 0));
107 return;
108 }
109 used[XINT (x, 0)] = 1;
110 }
111 printf ("operand%d", XINT (x, 0));
112 return;
113
114 case MATCH_OP_DUP:
115 printf ("gen_rtx_fmt_");
116 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (x, 1); i++)
117 printf ("e");
118 printf (" (GET_CODE (operand%d), ", XINT (x, 0));
119 if (GET_MODE (x) == VOIDmode)
120 printf ("GET_MODE (operand%d)", XINT (x, 0));
121 else
122 printf ("%smode", GET_MODE_NAME (GET_MODE (x)));
123 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (x, 1); i++)
124 {
125 printf (",\n\t\t");
126 gen_exp (XVECEXP (x, 1, i), subroutine_type, used);
127 }
128 printf (")");
129 return;
130
131 case MATCH_OPERATOR:
132 printf ("gen_rtx_fmt_");
133 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (x, 2); i++)
134 printf ("e");
135 printf (" (GET_CODE (operand%d)", XINT (x, 0));
136 printf (", %smode", GET_MODE_NAME (GET_MODE (x)));
137 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (x, 2); i++)
138 {
139 printf (",\n\t\t");
140 gen_exp (XVECEXP (x, 2, i), subroutine_type, used);
141 }
142 printf (")");
143 return;
144
145 case MATCH_PARALLEL:
146 case MATCH_PAR_DUP:
147 printf ("operand%d", XINT (x, 0));
148 return;
149
150 case MATCH_SCRATCH:
151 gen_rtx_scratch (x, subroutine_type);
152 return;
153
154 case PC:
155 printf ("pc_rtx");
156 return;
157 case RETURN:
158 printf ("ret_rtx");
159 return;
160 case SIMPLE_RETURN:
161 printf ("simple_return_rtx");
162 return;
163 case CLOBBER:
164 if (REG_P (XEXP (x, 0)))
165 {
166 printf ("gen_hard_reg_clobber (%smode, %i)", GET_MODE_NAME (GET_MODE (XEXP (x, 0))),
167 REGNO (XEXP (x, 0)));
168 return;
169 }
170 break;
171
172 case CC0:
173 printf ("cc0_rtx");
174 return;
175
176 case CONST_INT:
177 if (INTVAL (x) == 0)
178 printf ("const0_rtx");
179 else if (INTVAL (x) == 1)
180 printf ("const1_rtx");
181 else if (INTVAL (x) == -1)
182 printf ("constm1_rtx");
183 else if (-MAX_SAVED_CONST_INT <= INTVAL (x)
184 && INTVAL (x) <= MAX_SAVED_CONST_INT)
185 printf ("const_int_rtx[MAX_SAVED_CONST_INT + (%d)]",
186 (int) INTVAL (x));
187 else if (INTVAL (x) == STORE_FLAG_VALUE)
188 printf ("const_true_rtx");
189 else
190 {
191 printf ("GEN_INT (");
192 printf ("HOST_WIDE_INT_C (");
193 printf (HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_DEC, INTVAL (x));
194 printf (")");
195 printf (")");
196 }
197 return;
198
199 case CONST_DOUBLE:
200 case CONST_FIXED:
201 case CONST_WIDE_INT:
202 /* These shouldn't be written in MD files. Instead, the appropriate
203 routines in varasm.c should be called. */
204 gcc_unreachable ();
205
206 default:
207 break;
208 }
209
210 printf ("gen_rtx_");
211 print_code (code);
212 printf (" (");
213 if (!always_void_p (code))
214 {
215 printf ("%smode", GET_MODE_NAME (GET_MODE (x)));
216 sep = ",\n\t";
217 }
218
219 fmt = GET_RTX_FORMAT (code);
220 len = GET_RTX_LENGTH (code);
221 for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
222 {
223 if (fmt[i] == '0')
224 break;
225 fputs (sep, stdout);
226 switch (fmt[i])
227 {
228 case 'e': case 'u':
229 gen_exp (XEXP (x, i), subroutine_type, used);
230 break;
231
232 case 'i':
233 printf ("%u", XINT (x, i));
234 break;
235
236 case 'r':
237 printf ("%u", REGNO (x));
238 break;
239
240 case 's':
241 printf ("\"%s\"", XSTR (x, i));
242 break;
243
244 case 'E':
245 {
246 int j;
247 printf ("gen_rtvec (%d", XVECLEN (x, i));
248 for (j = 0; j < XVECLEN (x, i); j++)
249 {
250 printf (",\n\t\t");
251 gen_exp (XVECEXP (x, i, j), subroutine_type, used);
252 }
253 printf (")");
254 break;
255 }
256
257 default:
258 gcc_unreachable ();
259 }
260 sep = ",\n\t";
261 }
262 printf (")");
263}
264
265/* Output code to emit the instruction patterns in VEC, with each element
266 becoming a separate instruction. USED is as for gen_exp. */
267
268static void
269gen_emit_seq (rtvec vec, char *used)
270{
271 for (int i = 0, len = GET_NUM_ELEM (vec); i < len; ++i)
272 {
273 bool last_p = (i == len - 1);
274 rtx next = RTVEC_ELT (vec, i);
275 if (const char *name = get_emit_function (next))
276 {
277 printf (" %s (", name);
278 gen_exp (next, DEFINE_EXPAND, used);
279 printf (");\n");
280 if (!last_p && needs_barrier_p (next))
281 printf (" emit_barrier ();");
282 }
283 else
284 {
285 printf (" emit (");
286 gen_exp (next, DEFINE_EXPAND, used);
287 printf (", %s);\n", last_p ? "false" : "true");
288 }
289 }
290}
291
292/* Emit the given C code to the output file. The code is allowed to
293 fail if CAN_FAIL_P. NAME describes what we're generating,
294 for use in error messages. */
295
296static void
297emit_c_code (const char *code, bool can_fail_p, const char *name)
298{
299 if (can_fail_p)
300 printf ("#define FAIL return (end_sequence (), _val)\n");
301 else
302 printf ("#define FAIL _Pragma (\"GCC error \\\"%s cannot FAIL\\\"\")"
303 " (void)0\n", name);
304 printf ("#define DONE return (_val = get_insns (),"
305 "end_sequence (), _val)\n");
306
307 rtx_reader_ptr->print_md_ptr_loc (code);
308 printf ("%s\n", code);
309
310 printf ("#undef DONE\n");
311 printf ("#undef FAIL\n");
312}
313
314/* Generate the `gen_...' function for a DEFINE_INSN. */
315
316static void
317gen_insn (md_rtx_info *info)
318{
319 struct pattern_stats stats;
320 int i;
321
322 /* See if the pattern for this insn ends with a group of CLOBBERs of (hard)
323 registers or MATCH_SCRATCHes. If so, store away the information for
324 later. */
325
326 rtx insn = info->def;
327 if (XVEC (insn, 1))
328 {
329 int has_hard_reg = 0;
330
331 for (i = XVECLEN (insn, 1) - 1; i > 0; i--)
332 {
333 if (GET_CODE (XVECEXP (insn, 1, i)) != CLOBBER)
334 break;
335
336 if (REG_P (XEXP (XVECEXP (insn, 1, i), 0)))
337 has_hard_reg = 1;
338 else if (GET_CODE (XEXP (XVECEXP (insn, 1, i), 0)) != MATCH_SCRATCH)
339 break;
340 }
341
342 if (i != XVECLEN (insn, 1) - 1)
343 {
344 struct clobber_pat *p;
345 struct clobber_ent *link = XNEW (struct clobber_ent);
346 int j;
347
348 link->code_number = info->index;
349
350 /* See if any previous CLOBBER_LIST entry is the same as this
351 one. */
352
353 for (p = clobber_list; p; p = p->next)
354 {
355 if (p->first_clobber != i + 1
356 || XVECLEN (p->pattern, 1) != XVECLEN (insn, 1))
357 continue;
358
359 for (j = i + 1; j < XVECLEN (insn, 1); j++)
360 {
361 rtx old_rtx = XEXP (XVECEXP (p->pattern, 1, j), 0);
362 rtx new_rtx = XEXP (XVECEXP (insn, 1, j), 0);
363
364 /* OLD and NEW_INSN are the same if both are to be a SCRATCH
365 of the same mode,
366 or if both are registers of the same mode and number. */
367 if (! (GET_MODE (old_rtx) == GET_MODE (new_rtx)
368 && ((GET_CODE (old_rtx) == MATCH_SCRATCH
369 && GET_CODE (new_rtx) == MATCH_SCRATCH)
370 || (REG_P (old_rtx) && REG_P (new_rtx)
371 && REGNO (old_rtx) == REGNO (new_rtx)))))
372 break;
373 }
374
375 if (j == XVECLEN (insn, 1))
376 break;
377 }
378
379 if (p == 0)
380 {
381 p = XNEW (struct clobber_pat);
382
383 p->insns = 0;
384 p->pattern = insn;
385 p->first_clobber = i + 1;
386 p->next = clobber_list;
387 p->has_hard_reg = has_hard_reg;
388 clobber_list = p;
389 }
390
391 link->next = p->insns;
392 p->insns = link;
393 }
394 }
395
396 /* Don't mention instructions whose names are the null string
397 or begin with '*'. They are in the machine description just
398 to be recognized. */
399 if (XSTR (insn, 0)[0] == 0 || XSTR (insn, 0)[0] == '*')
400 return;
401
402 printf ("/* %s:%d */\n", info->loc.filename, info->loc.lineno);
403
404 /* Find out how many operands this function has. */
405 get_pattern_stats (&stats, XVEC (insn, 1));
406 if (stats.max_dup_opno > stats.max_opno)
407 fatal_at (info->loc, "match_dup operand number has no match_operand");
408
409 /* Output the function name and argument declarations. */
410 printf ("rtx\ngen_%s (", XSTR (insn, 0));
411 if (stats.num_generator_args)
412 for (i = 0; i < stats.num_generator_args; i++)
413 if (i)
414 printf (",\n\trtx operand%d ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED", i);
415 else
416 printf ("rtx operand%d ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED", i);
417 else
418 printf ("void");
419 printf (")\n");
420 printf ("{\n");
421
422 /* Output code to construct and return the rtl for the instruction body. */
423
424 rtx pattern = add_implicit_parallel (XVEC (insn, 1));
425 /* ??? This is the traditional behavior, but seems suspect. */
426 char *used = (XVECLEN (insn, 1) == 1
427 ? NULL
428 : XCNEWVEC (char, stats.num_generator_args));
429 printf (" return ");
430 gen_exp (pattern, DEFINE_INSN, used);
431 printf (";\n}\n\n");
432 XDELETEVEC (used);
433}
434
435/* Generate the `gen_...' function for a DEFINE_EXPAND. */
436
437static void
438gen_expand (md_rtx_info *info)
439{
440 struct pattern_stats stats;
441 int i;
442 char *used;
443
444 rtx expand = info->def;
445 if (strlen (XSTR (expand, 0)) == 0)
446 fatal_at (info->loc, "define_expand lacks a name");
447 if (XVEC (expand, 1) == 0)
448 fatal_at (info->loc, "define_expand for %s lacks a pattern",
449 XSTR (expand, 0));
450
451 /* Find out how many operands this function has. */
452 get_pattern_stats (&stats, XVEC (expand, 1));
453 if (stats.min_scratch_opno != -1
454 && stats.min_scratch_opno <= MAX (stats.max_opno, stats.max_dup_opno))
455 fatal_at (info->loc, "define_expand for %s needs to have match_scratch "
456 "numbers above all other operands", XSTR (expand, 0));
457
458 /* Output the function name and argument declarations. */
459 printf ("rtx\ngen_%s (", XSTR (expand, 0));
460 if (stats.num_generator_args)
461 for (i = 0; i < stats.num_generator_args; i++)
462 if (i)
463 printf (",\n\trtx operand%d", i);
464 else
465 printf ("rtx operand%d", i);
466 else
467 printf ("void");
468 printf (")\n");
469 printf ("{\n");
470
471 /* If we don't have any C code to write, only one insn is being written,
472 and no MATCH_DUPs are present, we can just return the desired insn
473 like we do for a DEFINE_INSN. This saves memory. */
474 if ((XSTR (expand, 3) == 0 || *XSTR (expand, 3) == '\0')
475 && stats.max_opno >= stats.max_dup_opno
476 && XVECLEN (expand, 1) == 1)
477 {
478 printf (" return ");
479 gen_exp (XVECEXP (expand, 1, 0), DEFINE_EXPAND, NULL);
480 printf (";\n}\n\n");
481 return;
482 }
483
484 /* For each operand referred to only with MATCH_DUPs,
485 make a local variable. */
486 for (i = stats.num_generator_args; i <= stats.max_dup_opno; i++)
487 printf (" rtx operand%d;\n", i);
488 printf (" rtx_insn *_val = 0;\n");
489 printf (" start_sequence ();\n");
490
491 /* The fourth operand of DEFINE_EXPAND is some code to be executed
492 before the actual construction.
493 This code expects to refer to `operands'
494 just as the output-code in a DEFINE_INSN does,
495 but here `operands' is an automatic array.
496 So copy the operand values there before executing it. */
497 if (XSTR (expand, 3) && *XSTR (expand, 3))
498 {
499 printf (" {\n");
500 if (stats.num_operand_vars > 0)
501 printf (" rtx operands[%d];\n", stats.num_operand_vars);
502
503 /* Output code to copy the arguments into `operands'. */
504 for (i = 0; i < stats.num_generator_args; i++)
505 printf (" operands[%d] = operand%d;\n", i, i);
506
507 /* Output the special code to be executed before the sequence
508 is generated. */
509 optab_pattern p;
510 bool can_fail_p = true;
511 if (find_optab (&p, XSTR (expand, 0)))
512 {
513 gcc_assert (p.op < NUM_OPTABS);
514 if (nofail_optabs[p.op])
515 can_fail_p = false;
516 }
517 emit_c_code (XSTR (expand, 3), can_fail_p, XSTR (expand, 0));
518
519 /* Output code to copy the arguments back out of `operands'
520 (unless we aren't going to use them at all). */
521 if (XVEC (expand, 1) != 0)
522 {
523 for (i = 0; i <= MAX (stats.max_opno, stats.max_dup_opno); i++)
524 {
525 printf (" operand%d = operands[%d];\n", i, i);
526 printf (" (void) operand%d;\n", i);
527 }
528 }
529 printf (" }\n");
530 }
531
532 used = XCNEWVEC (char, stats.num_operand_vars);
533 gen_emit_seq (XVEC (expand, 1), used);
534 XDELETEVEC (used);
535
536 /* Call `get_insns' to extract the list of all the
537 insns emitted within this gen_... function. */
538
539 printf (" _val = get_insns ();\n");
540 printf (" end_sequence ();\n");
541 printf (" return _val;\n}\n\n");
542}

544/* Like gen_expand, but generates insns resulting from splitting SPLIT. */
545
546static void
547gen_split (md_rtx_info *info)
548{
549 struct pattern_stats stats;
550 int i;
551 rtx split = info->def;
552 const char *const name =
553 ((GET_CODE (split) == DEFINE_PEEPHOLE2) ? "peephole2" : "split");
554 const char *unused;
555 char *used;
556
557 if (XVEC (split, 0) == 0)
558 fatal_at (info->loc, "%s lacks a pattern",
559 GET_RTX_NAME (GET_CODE (split)));
560 else if (XVEC (split, 2) == 0)
561 fatal_at (info->loc, "%s lacks a replacement pattern",
562 GET_RTX_NAME (GET_CODE (split)));
563
564 /* Find out how many operands this function has. */
565
566 get_pattern_stats (&stats, XVEC (split, 2));
567 unused = (stats.num_operand_vars == 0 ? " ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED" : "");
568 used = XCNEWVEC (char, stats.num_operand_vars);
569
570 /* Output the prototype, function name and argument declarations. */
571 if (GET_CODE (split) == DEFINE_PEEPHOLE2)
572 {
573 printf ("extern rtx_insn *gen_%s_%d (rtx_insn *, rtx *);\n",
574 name, info->index);
575 printf ("rtx_insn *\ngen_%s_%d (rtx_insn *curr_insn ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,"
576 " rtx *operands%s)\n",
577 name, info->index, unused);
578 }
579 else
580 {
581 printf ("extern rtx_insn *gen_split_%d (rtx_insn *, rtx *);\n",
582 info->index);
583 printf ("rtx_insn *\ngen_split_%d "
584 "(rtx_insn *curr_insn ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, rtx *operands%s)\n",
585 info->index, unused);
586 }
587 printf ("{\n");
588
589 /* Declare all local variables. */
590 for (i = 0; i < stats.num_operand_vars; i++)
591 printf (" rtx operand%d;\n", i);
592 printf (" rtx_insn *_val = NULL;\n");
593
594 if (GET_CODE (split) == DEFINE_PEEPHOLE2)
595 output_peephole2_scratches (split);
596
597 printf (" if (dump_file)\n");
598 printf (" fprintf (dump_file, \"Splitting with gen_%s_%d\\n\");\n",
599 name, info->index);
600
601 printf (" start_sequence ();\n");
602
603 /* The fourth operand of DEFINE_SPLIT is some code to be executed
604 before the actual construction. */
605
606 if (XSTR (split, 3))
607 emit_c_code (XSTR (split, 3), true, name);
608
609 /* Output code to copy the arguments back out of `operands' */
610 for (i = 0; i < stats.num_operand_vars; i++)
611 {
612 printf (" operand%d = operands[%d];\n", i, i);
613 printf (" (void) operand%d;\n", i);
614 }
615
616 gen_emit_seq (XVEC (split, 2), used);
617
618 /* Call `get_insns' to make a list of all the
619 insns emitted within this gen_... function. */
620
621 printf (" _val = get_insns ();\n");
622 printf (" end_sequence ();\n");
623 printf (" return _val;\n}\n\n");
624
625 free (used);
626}
627
628/* Write a function, `add_clobbers', that is given a PARALLEL of sufficient
629 size for the insn and an INSN_CODE, and inserts the required CLOBBERs at
630 the end of the vector. */
631
632static void
633output_add_clobbers (void)
634{
635 struct clobber_pat *clobber;
636 struct clobber_ent *ent;
637 int i;
638
639 printf ("\n\nvoid\nadd_clobbers (rtx pattern ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, int insn_code_number)\n");
640 printf ("{\n");
641 printf (" switch (insn_code_number)\n");
642 printf (" {\n");
643
644 for (clobber = clobber_list; clobber; clobber = clobber->next)
645 {
646 for (ent = clobber->insns; ent; ent = ent->next)
647 printf (" case %d:\n", ent->code_number);
648
649 for (i = clobber->first_clobber; i < XVECLEN (clobber->pattern, 1); i++)
650 {
651 printf (" XVECEXP (pattern, 0, %d) = ", i);
652 gen_exp (XVECEXP (clobber->pattern, 1, i),
653 GET_CODE (clobber->pattern), NULL);
654 printf (";\n");
655 }
656
657 printf (" break;\n\n");
658 }
659
660 printf (" default:\n");
661 printf (" gcc_unreachable ();\n");
662 printf (" }\n");
663 printf ("}\n");
664}
665
666/* Write a function, `added_clobbers_hard_reg_p' that is given an insn_code
667 number that will have clobbers added (as indicated by `recog') and returns
668 1 if those include a clobber of a hard reg or 0 if all of them just clobber
669 SCRATCH. */
670
671static void
672output_added_clobbers_hard_reg_p (void)
673{
674 struct clobber_pat *clobber;
675 struct clobber_ent *ent;
676 int clobber_p, used;
677
678 printf ("\n\nint\nadded_clobbers_hard_reg_p (int insn_code_number)\n");
679 printf ("{\n");
680 printf (" switch (insn_code_number)\n");
681 printf (" {\n");
682
683 for (clobber_p = 0; clobber_p <= 1; clobber_p++)
684 {
685 used = 0;
686 for (clobber = clobber_list; clobber; clobber = clobber->next)
687 if (clobber->has_hard_reg == clobber_p)
688 for (ent = clobber->insns; ent; ent = ent->next)
689 {
690 printf (" case %d:\n", ent->code_number);
691 used++;
692 }
693
694 if (used)
695 printf (" return %d;\n\n", clobber_p);
696 }
697
698 printf (" default:\n");
699 printf (" gcc_unreachable ();\n");
700 printf (" }\n");
701 printf ("}\n");
702}
703
704/* Generate code to invoke find_free_register () as needed for the
705 scratch registers used by the peephole2 pattern in SPLIT. */
706
707static void
708output_peephole2_scratches (rtx split)
709{
710 int i;
711 int insn_nr = 0;
712 bool first = true;
713
714 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (split, 0); i++)
715 {
716 rtx elt = XVECEXP (split, 0, i);
717 if (GET_CODE (elt) == MATCH_SCRATCH)
718 {
719 int last_insn_nr = insn_nr;
720 int cur_insn_nr = insn_nr;
721 int j;
722 for (j = i + 1; j < XVECLEN (split, 0); j++)
723 if (GET_CODE (XVECEXP (split, 0, j)) == MATCH_DUP)
724 {
725 if (XINT (XVECEXP (split, 0, j), 0) == XINT (elt, 0))
726 last_insn_nr = cur_insn_nr;
727 }
728 else if (GET_CODE (XVECEXP (split, 0, j)) != MATCH_SCRATCH)
729 cur_insn_nr++;
730
731 if (first)
732 {
733 printf (" HARD_REG_SET _regs_allocated;\n");
734 printf (" CLEAR_HARD_REG_SET (_regs_allocated);\n");
735 first = false;
736 }
737
738 printf (" if ((operands[%d] = peep2_find_free_register (%d, %d, \"%s\", %smode, &_regs_allocated)) == NULL_RTX)\n\
739 return NULL;\n",
740 XINT (elt, 0),
741 insn_nr, last_insn_nr,
742 XSTR (elt, 1),
743 GET_MODE_NAME (GET_MODE (elt)));
744
745 }
746 else if (GET_CODE (elt) != MATCH_DUP)
747 insn_nr++;
748 }
749}
750
751int
752main (int argc, const char **argv)
753{
754 progname = "genemit";
755
756 if (!init_rtx_reader_args (argc, argv))
757 return (FATAL_EXIT_CODE);
758
759#define DEF_INTERNAL_OPTAB_FN(NAME, FLAGS, OPTAB, TYPE) \
760 nofail_optabs[OPTAB##_optab] = true;
761#include "internal-fn.def"
762
763 /* Assign sequential codes to all entries in the machine description
764 in parallel with the tables in insn-output.c. */
765
766 printf ("/* Generated automatically by the program `genemit'\n\
767from the machine description file `md'. */\n\n");
768
769 printf ("#include \"config.h\"\n");
770 printf ("#include \"system.h\"\n");
771 printf ("#include \"coretypes.h\"\n");
772 printf ("#include \"backend.h\"\n");
773 printf ("#include \"predict.h\"\n");
774 printf ("#include \"tree.h\"\n");
775 printf ("#include \"rtl.h\"\n");
776 printf ("#include \"alias.h\"\n");
777 printf ("#include \"varasm.h\"\n");
778 printf ("#include \"stor-layout.h\"\n");
779 printf ("#include \"calls.h\"\n");
780 printf ("#include \"memmodel.h\"\n");
781 printf ("#include \"tm_p.h\"\n");
782 printf ("#include \"flags.h\"\n");
783 printf ("#include \"insn-config.h\"\n");
784 printf ("#include \"expmed.h\"\n");
785 printf ("#include \"dojump.h\"\n");
786 printf ("#include \"explow.h\"\n");
787 printf ("#include \"emit-rtl.h\"\n");
788 printf ("#include \"stmt.h\"\n");
789 printf ("#include \"expr.h\"\n");
790 printf ("#include \"insn-codes.h\"\n");
791 printf ("#include \"optabs.h\"\n");
792 printf ("#include \"dfp.h\"\n");
793 printf ("#include \"output.h\"\n");
794 printf ("#include \"recog.h\"\n");
795 printf ("#include \"df.h\"\n");
796 printf ("#include \"resource.h\"\n");
797 printf ("#include \"reload.h\"\n");
798 printf ("#include \"diagnostic-core.h\"\n");
799 printf ("#include \"regs.h\"\n");
800 printf ("#include \"tm-constrs.h\"\n");
801 printf ("#include \"ggc.h\"\n");
802 printf ("#include \"dumpfile.h\"\n");
803 printf ("#include \"target.h\"\n\n");
804
805 /* Read the machine description. */
806
807 md_rtx_info info;
808 while (read_md_rtx (&info))
809 switch (GET_CODE (info.def))
810 {
811 case DEFINE_INSN:
812 gen_insn (&info);
813 break;
814
815 case DEFINE_EXPAND:
816 printf ("/* %s:%d */\n", info.loc.filename, info.loc.lineno);
817 gen_expand (&info);
818 break;
819
820 case DEFINE_SPLIT:
821 printf ("/* %s:%d */\n", info.loc.filename, info.loc.lineno);
822 gen_split (&info);
823 break;
824
825 case DEFINE_PEEPHOLE2:
826 printf ("/* %s:%d */\n", info.loc.filename, info.loc.lineno);
827 gen_split (&info);
828 break;
829
830 default:
831 break;
832 }
833
834 /* Write out the routines to add CLOBBERs to a pattern and say whether they
835 clobber a hard reg. */
836 output_add_clobbers ();
837 output_added_clobbers_hard_reg_p ();
838
839 fflush (stdout);
840 return (ferror (stdout) != 0 ? FATAL_EXIT_CODE : SUCCESS_EXIT_CODE);
841}
